===Etymology 1===
Old English {{term|bregdan|breġdan|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro}} {{recons|bregdan|lang=gem-pro}}. Cognate with Dutch {{term|breien|lang=nl}}.

====Alternative forms====
* [[brayde]] {{qualifier|obsolete}}, [[breyde]] {{qualifier|obsolete}}

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA|/bɹeɪd/}}
* {{rhymes|eɪd}}

====Verb====
{{en-verb|braids|braiding|braided|'''[[braided]]''' ''or obsolete'' '''[[browden]]'''}}

# {{obsolete}} {{transitive}} To make a sudden movement with, to [[jerk]].
# {{archaic}} {{intransitive}} To [[start]] into motion.
# {{transitive}} To weave together, [[intertwine]] (strands of [[fibers]], [[ribbon]]s, etc.); to arrange (hair) in braids.

